{"title": "Memorials of a Tour on the Continent 1820", "description": "In 1820 William Wordsworth, in company with his wife Mary and sister Dorothy, undertook a tour of continental Europe, visiting Belgium, Germany, Switzerland and France. The journey followed the approximate route of Wordsworth's youthful walking tour in 1790, but in the opposite direction.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThese poems record his memories of the tour and contrast them with his memories of the earlier journey.\r\n<br><br>\r\n(Summary by Alan Mapstone) ", "duration": 3867, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1639", "name": "William Wordsworth"}], "coverArt": null, "copyright_year": "1822", "genres": ["Lyric"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Alan Mapstone"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Alan Mapstone"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Bruce Kachuk"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Dedication", "readers": [7170], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/memorialtouronthecontinent1820_2603_librivox/tour1820_00_wordsworth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 119}, {"section": 1, "title": "Fish Women. - on Landing at Calais", "readers": [7170], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/memorialtouronthecontinent1820_2603_librivox/tour1820_01_wordsworth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 89}, {"section": 2, "title": "Bruges", "readers": [7170], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/memorialtouronthecontinent1820_2603_librivox/tour1820_02_wordsworth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 85}, {"section": 3, "title": "Bruges", "readers": [7170], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/memorialtouronthecontinent1820_2603_librivox/tour1820_03_wordsworth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 85}, {"section": 4, "title": "After Visiting the Field of Waterloo", "readers": [7170], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/memorialtouronthecontinent1820_2603_librivox/tour1820_04_wordsworth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 92}, {"section": 5, "title": "Scenery between Namur and Liege"